FBIS4-36964 "drnes115_l_94003" FBIS-NES-94-115 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 ISRAEL IDF Officer on Cooperation With Palestinians IDF Officer on Cooperation With Palestinians TA1406130794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0830 GMT 14 Jun 94 TA1406130794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Hebrew BFN [Text] Brigadier General Yom-Tov Sami', head of the Israeli-Palestinian liaison committee, says that the joint IDF [Israel Defense Forces] and Palestinian police headquarters have proven themselves a great success. Sami' said the security situation in the autonomous areas is satisfactory, and voiced optimism concerning the Gaza-Jericho agreement. He added, however, that unless the economic situation in the Gaza Strip improves, the security situation could deteriorate. Our correspondent Geva' Qra'-'Oz reports that Brig. Gen. Sami' divulged that in the framework of their preparations for Yasir 'Arafat's arrival in the Gaza Strip, the Palestinians have started preparing a helicopter landing pad in Gaza, despite the fact that they are not authorized to do so.
